# Gyumri Tour Guide - OpenStreetMap Migration Walkthrough

I have successfully completed the migration to the new OpenStreetMap ([gyumri_places.json](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/openstreetmap/gyumri_places.json)) dataset!

The bot will now generate tour routes using the comprehensive dataset fetched from the [openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/openstreetmap/openstreetmap_collect_gyumri.py) script.

## What was changed

### 1. [data_gyumri.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/data_gyumri.py)
- We shifted the default json loading priority to look for [openstreetmap/gyumri_places.json](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/openstreetmap/gyumri_places.json) first.
- Re-wrote the dataset parsing logic to be able to safely consume the heavily nested `tags` dictionary typical of OpenStreetMap data, while maintaining backward compatibility with the old OpenTripMap dataset.
- Added logic to automatically glean the `category` of a location depending on its combination of OpenStreetMap tags (`amenity`, `tourism`, `historic`).
- Added robust Bilingual Name parsing logic (parsing out `name:en` or `name:ru` with a fallback to the native [name](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/llm.py#86-90)).
- Auto-generated a basic `short_description` from available tags if the OSM dataset did not have a dedicated description string (for example, combining `cuisine` tags and formatting them).

### 2. [routing.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/routing.py)
- Integrated the new robust naming scheme (`name_ru` -> `name_en` -> [name](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/llm.py#86-90) -> [id](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/main.py#35-40) fallback) into both [generate_programs](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/routing.py#6-58) and [format_program_options](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/routing.py#60-100).
- Adjusted the `< 1.5` chill walk filter to cast the distance to `float` as a safety precaution against mismatched data types.

### 3. [llm.py](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/llm.py)
- Abstracted the [get_name_and_desc](file:///c:/Users/401-15/Desktop/python/langchain_version_2/llm.py#86-90) naming logic into a helper function so that the LLM continues referencing the places properly when building its prompt context array.

## Verification
I ran a test Python script generating programs natively from the newly updated functions and confirmed that:
1. Coordinates matched places accurately.
2. The bot sorted places successfully into their proper route buckets (Classic, Food, Chill).
3. OpenStreetMap tags were correctly turned into readable point-of-interest titles (e.g. `I Love Gyumri`, `KFC`, `Тар-ту`).
